{"msg_id":"19c2f701-2f36-4611-bf1f-08b039dcaaf5","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775783839260632010,"operation":"work:create","payload":{"for":"cd41913b6aa59679a5499dbc9e974c08cb0b06fe8060b4db04e605c9ce5c9a50","id":"ready-760","priority":"p1","title":"rd init --relay: create project campfires on hosted relay for multi-machine portability","type":"task"},"tags":["work:create"],"sender":"cd41913b6aa59679a5499dbc9e974c08cb0b06fe8060b4db04e605c9ce5c9a50"}
{"msg_id":"8fdfb64a-689a-4c2a-b2bf-ed5bbf0ff01b","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775783862022771250,"operation":"work:update","payload":{"context":"[2026-04-10T01:17Z] ## Problem\n\nrd init creates filesystem-only campfires. When moving between machines (surface, workshop, trainer), each machine gets its own campfire with its own items — total etch-a-sketch brain.\n\n## Required\n\nAdd --relay flag to rd init so project campfires are created on the hosted relay (mcp.east.getcampfire.dev/api). cf 0.17.4 already supports this:\n\n  cf create --relay https://mcp.east.getcampfire.dev/api\n\nThe demos at campfire/test/demo/ (03-07, 11-12) prove relay transport works: create, join via beacon, read, send, beacon-based discovery.\n\n## Scope\n\n1. rd init --relay \u003curl\u003e — pass --relay to cf create when creating the project campfire\n2. rd init --join \u003cbeacon\u003e — join an existing project campfire on another machine (skip create, join via beacon, write .ready/config.json)\n3. .ready/config.json already stores campfire_id — add transport metadata (relay URL, beacon) so rd sync knows how to reach it\n4. rd sync pull should work unchanged — cf SDK handles relay transport transparently once joined\n\n## Multi-machine workflow after this ships\n\nMachine 1 (first init):\n  cd ~/projects/mallcop \u0026\u0026 rd init --relay https://mcp.east.getcampfire.dev/api\n  # shares beacon\n\nMachine 2 (join):  \n  cd ~/projects/mallcop \u0026\u0026 rd init --join \u003cbeacon\u003e\n  # same campfire, same items, same identity (via cf home link)\n\n## Evidence\n\n- campfire/test/demo/04-relay-beacon-join.sh — beacon join over relay works\n- campfire/test/demo/03-relay-join-once-read-many.sh — cursor-based read works over relay\n- campfire/test/demo/12-rejoin-upgrade.sh — rejoin after disconnect works, messages preserved\n\n## Not in scope\n\n- Identity portability across machines (cf home link exists, separate concern)\n- Migrating existing filesystem campfires to relay (future item)\n- Offline-first with relay sync (rd sync already buffers to pending.jsonl)","target":"19c2f701-2f36-4611-bf1f-08b039dcaaf5"},"tags":["work:update"],"sender":"cd41913b6aa59679a5499dbc9e974c08cb0b06fe8060b4db04e605c9ce5c9a50"}
{"msg_id":"e2a80900-9178-4464-8cea-e856d0b5d58d","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775784171252413254,"operation":"work:claim","payload":{"target":"19c2f701-2f36-4611-bf1f-08b039dcaaf5"},"tags":["work:claim"],"sender":"cd41913b6aa59679a5499dbc9e974c08cb0b06fe8060b4db04e605c9ce5c9a50"}
{"msg_id":"6279931e-6998-4754-905f-8290a40c7d39","campfire_id":"670f815159f88220981e79b7cbbc5e98432d73771c215b7d2082ec818b74329a","timestamp":1775785159564930209,"operation":"work:close","payload":{"reason":"Implemented rd init relay support: (1) rd init reads transport.relay from cf config cascade — when set, creates campfires on hosted relay via cfhttp.RegisterOnRelay instead of filesystem. (2) rd init --join \u003cbeacon\u003e joins existing project campfire on another machine. (3) SyncConfig stores relay_url and beacon for multi-machine portability. (4) Upgraded campfire SDK v0.14→v0.17.5, fixed all breaking API changes. (5) All tests pass including hosted e2e topology test.","resolution":"done","target":"19c2f701-2f36-4611-bf1f-08b039dcaaf5"},"tags":["work:close"],"sender":"cd41913b6aa59679a5499dbc9e974c08cb0b06fe8060b4db04e605c9ce5c9a50"}
